m_q.target_metric: ratio of reports between the most frequent and least frequent category, rounded to two decimal places
sub_questions: Identify the category with maximum # of Reports
Identify the category with minimum # of Reports
Round result to two decimal places

scale_issues: Percentage column contains '%' symbol and needs cleaning for numerical operations

format_notes: File contains 29 rows (28 data rows + header)
Category names may contain commas within quotes

constraints: Rank values should be unique and sequential
Sum of # of Reports should be consistent
Percentage values should sum to approximately 100%
derived_filters: Use all 28 category rows for analysis
statistical_tests: Check for missing values in # of Reports column
Verify Rank ordering matches # of Reports ordering
output_format_requirements: Ratio must be rounded to two decimal places
Result should be a single numerical value
